{"lemma":"عارٌ","slug":"عارٌ","root":"ع.#.ر","root_slug":"ع-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28508","n28523","n28887","n28902","n30978","n31188","n31181"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of عَرِيَ (ʕariya).","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"bare, naked, nude"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"stark, barren"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"blank"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"free of, devoid of, deprived of (with عَن (ʕan) or مِن (min))"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to roam, to wander"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shame, disgrace, ignominy","examples":[{"text":"Abu al-Aswad al-Du'ali\nلَا تَنْهَ عَنْ خُلُقٍ وَتَأْتِيَ مِثْلَهُ\nعَارٌ عَلَيْكَ إِذَا فَعَلْتَ عَظِيمُ\nlā tanha ʕan ḵuluqin wataʔtiya miṯlahu\nʕārun ʕalayka ʔiḏā faʕalta ʕaẓīmu\nDo not forbid a thing you do;","english":"If you do, shame on you."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of عَرِيَ (ʕariya, “to become naked”)\n\nMorphologically from the root ع ي ر (ʕ y r)."},"ipa":["/ʕaː.rin/","/ʕaː.ra/","/ʕaːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28508","headword_ar":"عارّ","root":"Er","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuEaAr~u","text_ar":"يُعَارُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraArN","text_ar":"عِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAr~apN","text_ar":"مُعَارَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and, (S, O, K,) as some say, (S, O,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ear~a","text_ar":"عَرَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (thus in the L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiraArN","text_ar":"عِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) with kesr; (K; [in one of my copies of the S"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraArN","text_ar":"عَرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuraArq","text_ar":"عُرَارق"},{"kind":"text","text":", which would be agreeable with analogy, I do not find;])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an ostrich [said of the male only])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cried; uttered a cry"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cries:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) like as they say of a female ostrich"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamarato","text_ar":"زَمَرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O: *) IKtt cites an assertion that it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra","text_ar":"عَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEuwru","text_ar":"يَعُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n28523","headword_ar":"عَارٌّ","root":"Er","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the mange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scab;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEar~u","text_ar":"اَعَرُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A'Obeyd, S, O;) which latter [in some of the copies of the K written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ear~N","text_ar":"عَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is applied in this sense to a man; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwrN","text_ar":"مَعْرُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a camel: (K:) or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected with, the disease called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eur~","text_ar":"عُرّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotar~N","text_ar":"مُعْتَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n28887","headword_ar":"عَارٍ","root":"Erw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraAhu","text_ar":"عَرَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first [and in others also] of the senses assigned to it above. (Msb.) En-Nábighah says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^atayotuka EaAriyFA xalaqFA viyaAbiY\n                      \n                     \n                        EalaY xawofK yuZan~u biYa AlZ~unuwnu"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"have come to thee, as a guest"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking thy beneficence, with my clothes old and worn out, in fear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"various"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thoughts being thought of me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S; one of my copies of which has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taZun~u","text_ar":"تَظُنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuZan~u","text_ar":"يُظَنُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28902","headword_ar":"عَارٍ","root":"ErY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuroyaAnN","text_ar":"عُرْيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAriY AlA^a$aAjiEi","text_ar":"عَارِى الاَشَاجِعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaEu","text_ar":"اَشْجَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAriY Alv~anoduw^atayoni","text_ar":"عَارِى الثَّنْدُوَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having no flesh on the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vanoduw^ataAni","text_ar":"ثَنْدُوَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two paps"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And [hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaq~u EaArK","text_ar":"الحَقُّ عَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The truth is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"naked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manifest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ejz","text_ar":"عجز"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30978","headword_ar":"عَارٌ","root":"Ewr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eyr","text_ar":"عير"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31188","headword_ar":"عَارٌ","root":"Eyr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A disgrace; a shame; a thing that occasions one's being reviled; a vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing for which one is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is to be, blamed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispraised;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(B, in TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewr","text_ar":"عور"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that necessarily occasions blame"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reproach,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disgrace:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyaArN","text_ar":"اَعْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAyiru","text_ar":"مَعَايِرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) of which the sing. is app. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyarapN","text_ar":"مَعْيَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) [is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyaArN","text_ar":"اَعْيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for it] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things for which one is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is to be, blamed, upbraided, reproached,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"found fault with;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAyibu","text_ar":"مَعَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n31181","headword_ar":"عَارَ","root":"Eyr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEiyru","text_ar":"يَعِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeyed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"عَارَ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went away in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into, the land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"country."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra","text_ar":"عَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, &c.,) aor. as above, (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaArN","text_ar":"عِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) or this is a simple subst., (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse, S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, and a dog, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hither and thither,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA,) which action is also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaAyarapN","text_ar":"مُعَايَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAyara","text_ar":"عَايَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though he had made his escape"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his master, going to and fro:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the same is said of news: (IKtt, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"escaped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"got loose, and went away hither and thither, by reason of his exceeding sprightliness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"escaped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"got loose, and went away at random:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away hither and thither, by reason of his sprightliness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strayed at random, nothing turning him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away at random, far from his master."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra","text_ar":"عَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor. as above, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came and went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moving to and fro."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra fiY Alqawomi yaDoribuhumo biAls~ayofi","text_ar":"عَارَ فِى القَوْمِ يَضْرِبُهُمْ بِالسَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayaraAnN","text_ar":"عَيَرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went and came among the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did mischief among them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smiting them with the sword."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArati AlqaSiydapu","text_ar":"عَارَتِ القَصِيدَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ode became current."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAra","text_ar":"عَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. as above, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyaArN","text_ar":"عِيَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayaraAnN","text_ar":"عَيَرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left his females"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2208},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that were seven months gone with young, and went away to others,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to cover them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKtt, L.) In [some of] the copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awolahaA","text_ar":"شَوْلَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awolahu","text_ar":"شَوْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is the reading in the Tahdheeb of IKtt [and in the CK]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArahu","text_ar":"عَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEiyruhu","text_ar":"يَعِيرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEuwruhu","text_ar":"يَعُورُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewr","text_ar":"عور"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or the aor. is not used, or it is scarcely ever used, (TA in the same art.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, took, and went away with, him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and K in the same art.:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K and TA in the same art.) See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewr","text_ar":"عور"},{"kind":"text","text":". You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eirotu vawobahu","text_ar":"عِرْتُ ثَوْبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away with, his garment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayorN EaArahu watiduhu","text_ar":"عَيْرٌ عَارَهُ وَتِدُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ass which his peg"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to which he was tethered]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by preventing his escape from wild beasts that attacked him]. (Meyd, TA. [See Freytag's Arab. Prov., ii. 87.])       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArahu","text_ar":"عَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor. as above,] also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He blamed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reproached, him; found fault with him; attributed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imputed to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charged him with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accused him of, a vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) [See also what next follows.]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","O","IKtt","S","Mgh","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}